{"lemma": "سَفِيهٌ", "slug": "سَفِيهٌ", "root": "س.ف.ه", "root_slug": "س-ف-ه", "root_link": "/words/roots/س-ف-ه", "pos": "ADJ", "pos_camel": "adj", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "سَفِيه", "root": "سفه", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 7}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["adj"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 2}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n20032"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%87%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "foolish", "fa": "نادان", "ur": "نادان", "tr": "ağır", "id": "bodoh", "bn": "মূর্খ", "es": "tonto", "fr": "sot", "de": "dumm", "ru": "глупый", "zh": "愚蠢的"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "adj", "gloss": "foolish, stupid, silly"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "ill-mannered", "examples": [{"text": "Al-Shafi'i\nيُخَاطِبُنِي السَّفِيهُ بِكُلِّ قُبْحٍ / فَأَكْرَهُ أَنْ أَكُونَ لَهُ مُجِيبًا\nيَزِيدُ سَفَاهَةً فَأَزِيدُ حِلْمًا / كَعُودٍ زَادَهُ الْإِحْرَاقُ طِيبًا\nyuḵāṭibuni as-safīhu bikulli qubḥin / faʔakrahu ʔan ʔakūna lahū mujīban\nyazīdu safāhatan faʔazīdu ḥilman / kaʕūdin zādahu l-ʔiḥrāqu ṭīban", "english": "(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/sa.fiːh/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n20032", "headword_ar": "سَفيِهٌ", "root": "sfh", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Having the quality termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safahN", "text_ar": "سَفَهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; i. e., accord. to the explanation of the primary signification of the latter, above,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Light;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in a state of motion, commotion,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "agitation:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] applied to a camel's nose-rein, (S, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "light:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "quivering;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA;) because of the she-camel's shaking it, and contending in pulling it. (TA: but there said to be, when thus applied, tropical.) Dhu-rRummeh says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "EalaY Zahori miqolaAtK safiyhK jadiyluhaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e. ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Upon the back of a she-camel that had brought forth but once and not conceived after,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whose nose-rein was light."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S. In the TA,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zimaAmuhaA", "text_ar": "زِمَامُهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is here put in the place of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jadiyluhaA", "text_ar": "جَدِيلُهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) And one says also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naAqapN safiyhapu AlzimaAmi", "text_ar": "نَاقَةٌ سَفِيهَةُ الزِمَامِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, TA,) meaning ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A she-camel whose nose-rein is light,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "quivering:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "light,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "agile, in pace"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "going."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA: in which this, also, is said to be tropical.) ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Lightwitted; light of intellect"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "understanding;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "deficient in intellect"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "understanding;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ignorant;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mujáhid, K, TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "weak; foolish, stupid, unsound in intellect"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "understanding, dull therein,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having little,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "no, intellect,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "understanding;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mujáhid, TA;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saAfihN", "text_ar": "سَافِهٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", also, [which is syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safiyhN", "text_ar": "سَفِيهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in all the senses mentioned above,] is expl. by IAar as having this last meaning of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "foolish, stupid,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.: (TA:) the fem. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safiyhapN", "text_ar": "سَفِيهَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb, K:) and the pl. of the masc., (K,) or of the masc. and fem., (Msb, TA,) is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sufahaA='u", "text_ar": "سُفَهَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb, K, TA,) and of both,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sifaAhN", "text_ar": "سِفَاهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and of the fem.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safiyhaAtN", "text_ar": "سَفِيهَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safaAy^ihu", "text_ar": "سَفَايِهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suf~ahN", "text_ar": "سُفَّهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K, TA.) In the Kur ii. 282,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safiyhFA", "text_ar": "سَفِيهًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means, accord. to Ibn-'Arafeh,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Ignorant of the ordinances,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "statutes; one who does not dictate well, and knows not what dictation is;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for he who is ignorant in all his circumstances may not deal with another upon credit: accord. to ISd,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ignorant or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Sagiyr", "text_ar": "صَغِير"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "under the age of puberty"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; not ignorant of dictating, as Lh asserts it to mean, because it is added, “ or not able to dictate, himself: ” this, says Er-Rághib, denotes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safah", "text_ar": "سَفَه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in respect of worldly matters: in the Kur lxxii. 4,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safiyhunaA", "text_ar": "سَفِيهُنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "denotes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safah", "text_ar": "سَفَه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in religion. (TA.) In the Kur iv. 4, the pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~ufahaA='", "text_ar": "السُّفَهَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is said to mean"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Women, and young children;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because they are ignorant of the proper object of expense: and I'Ab is related to have said that women are termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~uf~ahu", "text_ar": "السُّفَّهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~ufahaA='u", "text_ar": "السُّفَهَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Lh, TA:) Az, also, says that a woman is termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safiyhapN", "text_ar": "سَفِيهَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because of the weakness of her intellect, and because she does not manage well her property; and in like manner are termed children as long as they are not known to be characterized by maturity of intellect, and rectitude of actions, and good management of affairs. (TA.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vawobN safiyhN", "text_ar": "ثَوْبٌ سَفِيهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A garment,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "piece of cloth, badly woven; thin, flimsy, unsubstantial,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "scanty in the yarn."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, * TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "K", "TA", "Msb", "Lh"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}